  "description": "Melodica in its most grounded configuration — moderate buzz, low-mid filter, full pressure wobble. This is the melodica left in a humid room overnight: reeds swollen slightly, breath resistance higher, each note a small physical negotiation. Not pristine. Alive in the way only slightly broken things are. Jon Batiste knows this sound.",
